                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Personally, I like giving my pet a velium swiftblade for the 36% item haste on it, and then usually a summoned mage weapon with a proc.  Though you might want a weapon without a damage proc if you're relying on root though to keep the other mob off you when charm breaks.  Really though, nothing will make your pet more effective than a swiftblade, since it just ups the dps remarkably.
<br />

<br />
As for what a pet can wield, as far as I know, pets can wield any weapons you give them, same goes for armor (giving a charmed pet a set of mage-summoned armor can make a huge difference in tanking ability).   The key to getting it to dual wield though is giving it two weapons with different delays.  Generally, I give my pet the weapon with the higher delay first, then the lower delay weapon, and that works fine.  Don't know if you can give it to them in the reverse order, but I seem to remember that not working as well.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
