                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Gemgem wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Do you get the weapon back?
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
In order to get your weapons back, you (or your party) must be the ones that kill your pet.  
<br />

<br />
If your pet is killed my a mob that you are fighting or if you kill it while the mob is still alive, it's body will poof and so will anything you gave it.  
<br />

<br />
It's basically the same rules as geting the experience for killing the MOB.  If you get the credit, the body is there with everything you gave it.  If not it's all gone.
<br />

<br />
Iumarex Mistweaver
<br />
Coercer for Greater Druids
<br />
Quellious</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
