                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">"Does this work with only charmed pets?"
<br />

<br />
Works with pets/animations as well
<br />

<br />
"Do you get the weapon back?"
<br />

<br />
Only if player characters got credit for killing the pet/animation/charmed mob.
<br />

<br />
"At what level can you give pets a weapon?"
<br />

<br />
You can always give pets a weapon...it will only use it if the pet/animation "thinks" it's better than what they have (hence the really crappy stats on animated weapons).  Another note:  Charmed mobs/pets/animations will *NOT* weild a nodrop item.
<br />

<br />
"At what level do pets dual wield?"
<br />

<br />
At certain levels they do depending on class...if I remember right:
<br />

<br />
Mages - level 16 pets
<br />
Necros - level 29 pets
<br />
Enchanters - level 39 pets
<br />
Shadowknights - whatever their equivalent to the necro 29 pet is
<br />

<br />
"What is a good mob on which to practice?"
<br />

<br />
Probably decayed skeletons =)
<br />

<br />
Note:  As was stated before...some pets will NOT dual wield.  Some pets (depending on the model) will not wield a weapon at all!  Try charming a mob that you know will wield weapons.  Cast tricksters on it.  Hand a weapon.  It will not wield it...additionally...it will not be wielding it when it turns back into itself.  The reverse holds true as well.  If you get a mob that will not normally wield a weapon, you can turn it into a scarecrow and give it the weapons(s) then it will wield the weapons while it is a scarecrow.  If it turns back into its original form it will not be wielding them, but if you cast NDT on it again it will be wielding the weapons again.  The weapons have to be visibly equipped for them to work.  Usually, you can tell what models will give you this problem...they *never* have weapons equipped.  Mobs hardcoded not to dual wield will *never* dual wield no matter what you turn them into.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
