                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I've been giving the Frenzied Initiate in Tactics a Adjutant's Saber, then putting NDT on him and he's a proccing stunning machine.  I haven't exp'd in Tactics in about a month, but before I stopped and joined a raiding guild it was a deathly combination.  Just have to be extra careful or you'll get too close when charm breaks (Friend kept him snared) and get stunned.
<br />

<br />
Here's the Adjutant's Saber's proc:
<br />
Effect: Ethereal Stun
<br />
2: Stun(1.00 sec/65)
<br />
3: Decrease Hate by 200  (This doesn't seem to matter at all)
<br />

<br />
Also wanted to mention that if you want to keep your target mob rooted, don't cast NDT on your pet.  That proc breaks root and it procs a lot with the extra 120 dex that NDT gives.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
